[[bibliographystyle:acm]]

- "we consider the motion of a uniformly accelerated particle in
  $\mathbb{R}^3$, colliding elastically with a linear cone of
  half-angle \theta."

\begin{equation}
H = \frac{1}{2} \left[ p_r^2 + \frac{1}{r^2} \left( p_\theta^2 + \frac{ p_\phi^2 }{ \sin^2\theta}\right)\right] + g r \cos\theta.
\end{equation}

- The conserved quantities are:

#+BEGIN_CENTER
$H=E$, \hspace{1cm} and \hspace{1cm} $p_\phi=\ell_z$
#+END_CENTER





